Sharing Operators and the PI company on the Execution Date; 
“Carry Forward” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms); 
“Change” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 9; 
“Charge Effective Date” means:  
a. For Existing Sites: The Effective Date for all Existing Sites specified in Appendix 2 of Schedule 
1 (Site Access Availability); or 
b. For New Sites and New Build Sites: The earlier of (i) the effective date as mentioned in the 
Sharing Operator’s acceptance of the RFAI notice in accordance with Schedule 1 (Site Access 
Availability); or (ii) acceptance (or deemed approval) of the Site by the Sharing Operator in 
accordance with Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability), for all New Sites or New Build Sites;  
“Charges” means the charges for the sharing of Passive Infrastructure specified in Schedule 3 
(Charges); 
“Circles” means the 22 telecommunications service areas in India as defined by the Department 
of Telecommunications, Government of India; 
“Co-located Site” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms); 
“Contract Year” means any continuous period of 12 (twelve) months commencing on the 
Execution Date or an anniversary thereof; 
“COWs” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Cure Period Expiry Date” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and 
Maintenance Services);  
“Difficult Site” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Dispute” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 20.1; 
“Disputed Amount” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 6.4.1; 
“Dispute Resolution Procedure” means the procedure for the resolution of disputes described in 
Clause 20; 
“DoT” means the Department of Telecommunication, Ministry of Communications and 
Information Technology, Government of India; 
“Downtime” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services); 
“EB Availability” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services);  
“Effective Date” means the Closing Date (as defined under the Business Transfer Agreement);   
“EMF” has the meaning given to it in Clause 2.6.3;

Confidential 
Page 6 of 108 
“Energy Cost” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Event of Damage” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 15.1.4(a); 
“Execution Date” has the meaning given to that term in the Preamble; 
“Existing Sites” means the Sites specified in Appendix 2 of Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability) 
that are available for sharing; 
“Existing Sites Service Contracts” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard 
Site Access Terms); 
“Exit Amount” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms); 
“Feather Site” means any Site where the Sharing Operator utilizes the Passive Infrastructure in 
relation to the Sharing Operator's Standard Configuration specified in Schedule 1 (Site Access 
Availability); 
“Financial Year” means a 12 (twelve) month period commencing on 1 April of any calendar year 
and ending on 31 March of the subsequent calendar year; 
“Force Majeure Event” means an act or event affecting the performance by a Party of its 
obligations hereunder arising from events beyond its reasonable control including war, disaster, 
fire, flood, terrorist attack, order or directive of any court or competent Government Authority in 
India, for which a substitute third party is not reasonably available, provided in all cases that the 
Party whose performance is affected has taken all steps (if any) which it could reasonably be 
expected to have taken in order to prevent such act or event occurring; 
“Free Exit Entitlement” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access 
Terms); 
“Good Industry Practice” means the exercise of that degree of skill, care, diligence, prudence, 
foresight and judgement which would reasonably be expected from a skilled and experienced 
operator engaged in the provision of services similar to the passive infrastructure services to be 
provided by the PI company; 
“Government Authority” means and includes any statutory authority, Central, State or local 
governmental entity or instrumentality (including any ministry, department, political subdivision, 
agency, corporation or other person exercising the delegated authority of any such person or 
entity) having jurisdiction on behalf of the Republic of India (whether legislative, executive, 
regulatory, administrative, judicial or otherwise howsoever) over the subject matter of, or any 
matter pertaining to, this Agreement; either or both of the Parties, including without  limitation, 
the DoT, Ministry of Communications, Government of India, TRAI and/or any other Telecom 
Regulatory Authority including Telecommunication Engineering Centre (TEC);   
“Group Company” means, in respect of any company, that company, any company of which it is 
a Subsidiary (its “Holding Company”) and any other Subsidiaries of such Holding Company from 
time to time; 
“ICL” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms);

Confidential 
Page 7 of 108 
“Insolvency Event” occurs if a Party becomes bankrupt or insolvent or enters into a composition 
with its creditors generally, or any final resolution is passed for its winding up or bankruptcy or 
any petition or proceedings to wind up the Party have been admitted by a competent court of 
law (and such petition or proceedings are not disputed in good faith) or there is an attachment 
of or the levy or execution on a substantial part of the assets or business of the Party which is 
not remedied within 120 (one hundred twenty) days, or an encumbrance takes possession of the 
assets or business of the Party or a receiver, trustee, administrator or similar officer is appointed 
over all or a substantial part of its assets or business, or any procedure equivalent to any of the 
preceding matters occurs in any other jurisdiction with respect to that Party;  
“indemnifying party” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 14; 
“indemnified party” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 14; 
“Inspection Period” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Insurance Policies” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 15; 
“Intellectual Property Rights” means trademarks, service marks, trade names, domain names, 
logos, get-up, patents, inventions, registered and unregistered design rights, copyrights, semi-
conductor topography rights, database rights and all other similar rights in any part of the world 
(including Know-How) including, where such rights are obtained or enhanced by registration, any 
registration of such rights and applications and rights to apply for such registrations; 
“Know-How” means confidential and proprietary industrial and commercial information and 
techniques in any form including drawings, formulae, test results, reports, project reports and 
testing procedures, instruction and training manuals, tables of operating conditions, market 
forecasts, lists and particulars of customers and suppliers; 
“Law” means any statute, law, ordinance, rule, regulation, administrative interpretation, 
approval, press note, order, writ, injunction, directive, judgment or decree having the force of 
law issued by the Government of India or any of its ministries, departments, secretariats, 
agencies or any legislative body, court or tribunal, whether at the central, state or 
municipal/local level from time to time; 
“Legacy Sites” means Sites which have +24V power source as on the Effective Date;  
“Lite Site” means any Site where the Sharing Operator utilizes the Passive Infrastructure in 
accordance with the Sharing Operator's Standard Configuration specified in Schedule 1 (Site 
Access Availability); 
“Low Configuration Site” means any Site where the Sharing Operator utilizes the Passive 
Infrastructure in accordance with the Sharing Operator's Standard Configuration specified in 
Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Management Meeting” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 8.2.1;  
“Management Trigger Date” means the date following the expiry of six (6) months from the 
Effective Date, which shall be the date when the PI company shall have in place the necessary 
expertise for operation and maintenance of the Existing Sites in accordance with the provisions 
of this Agreement;

