of business; 
“Permitted Use” means the purpose of operating a mobile telecommunications network and 
providing mobile telecommunications services; 
“Personnel” means the employees, agents and subcontractors of the PI company or its 
subcontractors engaged in the provision of the Operation and Maintenance Services; 
“Premium Site” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Qualifying Site” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services); 
“Relationship Manager” means, as the context requires, the relationship manager of either the 
PI company or the Sharing Operator; 
“Relevant MSA” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 2.1.8;  
“Relocation” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 4.2.1; 
“Relocation Fees” means the costs associated with the relocation of any Site, including any 
Active Infrastructure, which shall be:  
a. the actual costs incurred by the Sharing Operator in connection with the relocation, subject 
to a maximum amount of INR 250,000 (Rupees Two hundred and fifty thousand) per Site, in 
case of all Sites (other than Special Sites and Transmission Hub Sites); and  
b. the actual costs incurred by the Sharing Operator in connection with the relocation of Active 
Infrastructure at a Site, in case of Special Sites and Transmission Hub Sites.  
“Rental Premium” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Rental Threshold” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges); 
“Right” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 22.4; 
“SACFA” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 2.6.2; 
“Second Inspection Period” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access 
Availability); 
“Security Deposit” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Service Order” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 2.1.2 and shall be in the form set 
out in Schedule 4;  
“Service Contract” means (a) each of the existing service contracts executed between the 
Sharing Operator and the PI Company prior to the Effective Date in relation to the Existing Sites 
for which the Sharing Operator is being provided Site Access Availability and Operation and 
Maintenance Services and such other services as may be agreed between the Sharing Operator 
and the PI company, which shall in each case be in accordance with the Standard Site Access 
Terms set out in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms); and (b) each service contract to be

