executed between the Sharing Operator and the PI company in relation to any particular Site, in 
respect of which the Sharing Operator is being provided Site Access Availability and Operation 
and Maintenance Services and such other services as may be agreed between the Sharing 
Operator and the PI company, which shall in each case be in accordance with the Standard Site 
Access Terms set out in Schedule 5 (Standard Site Access Terms);  
“Sharing Operator” or “Sharing Operators” has the meaning given to that term in the Preamble; 
“Sharing Operator Downtime” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and 
Maintenance Services); 
“Sharing Operator Equipment” means any equipment located (or to be located) at a Site and 
owned by the Sharing Operator or otherwise under the Sharing Operator’s management or 
control as specified in each applicable Service Order; 
“Sharing Operator Licence” means any mobile telecommunications licence granted by the DoT 
to the Sharing Operator for the Permitted Use; 
“Site Access Availability” in relation to a Site, means the availability of access to the Sharing 
Operator to the Passive Infrastructure at the Site in accordance with Schedule 1 (Site Access 
Availability);  
“Site Access Service Levels” means the service levels relating to Site Access Availability as set 
out in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Site Acquisition” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Site Proposal” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Site Request” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 1 (Site Access Availability); 
“Site” means each of the telecommunications sites owned or acquired and possessed by the PI 
company in the Circles in India; 
“Special Sites” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services);  
“Standard Rate” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Statement of Loss” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 15.1.4(b); 
“Status Lock-in Period” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Strategic Site” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services);  
“Subsidiary” has the same meaning as in the (Indian) Companies Act, 2013;  
“Taxes” means all statutory, governmental, state, provincial, local governmental or municipal 
taxes impositions, duties, contributions, rates, cess, fees and levies, existing or future, and shall 
include any increases therein or any other similar charges, whenever and wherever imposed;

Confidential 
