“Term” means the term of this Agreement, as set out in Clause 11.1; 
“Termination Entitlement” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 5 (Standard Site 
Access Terms); 
“Termination Notice” means a notice in writing in accordance with Clause 11 served by one 
Party on the other to initiate the termination of this Agreement; 
“Territory Circles” means and includes the following Circles: Assam, Bihar, Himachal Pradesh, 
Madhya Pradesh, North East, Orissa and Jammu & Kashmir; 
“TOC” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance Services); 
“Total Rate” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 3 (Charges);  
“Transitional Site” means any Site where the Sharing Operator utilizes the Passive Infrastructure 
in accordance with the Sharing Operator's Standard Configuration specified in Schedule 1 (Site 
Access Availability); 
“Transmission Hub Site” means a Site with transmission links which provides transmission 
connectivity to multiple other Sites. An initial list of such sites is mentioned in Part A of Schedule 
7; 
“Transmission Repeater Site” means any Site where Sharing Operator has installed transmission 
equipment only and has not installed Base Transceiver Station (BTS), Node B and/or e-Node B; 
“Uptime” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and Maintenance 
Services);  
“Uptime Failure Period” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and 
Maintenance Services);  
“Uptime Service Level” has the meaning given to that term in Schedule 2 (Operation and 
Maintenance Services). 
“VIL” has the meaning given to that term in the Preamble; 
“VMSL” has the meaning given to that term in the Preamble; and 
“WPC” has the meaning given to that term in Clause 2.6.2. 
1.2 
Modification etc. of Statutes 
References to a statute or statutory provision include: 
1.2.1 
that statute or provision as from time to time modified, re-enacted or consolidated 
whether before or after the Execution Date; 
1.2.2 
any past statute or statutory provision (as from time to time modified, re-enacted or 
consolidated) which that statute or provision has directly or indirectly replaced; and 
1.2.3 
any subordinate legislation made from time to time under that statute or statutory 
provision which is in force at the Execution Date.
